Thanks for sharing 

but

if you do something do it right.
You're using a stone age codec. Get LAME 3.98.4 here
http://www.rarewares.org/mp3-lame-bundle.php

Using LAME 3.92 in 2010 is fucking gay!
Also, using 320kbps instead of -V 0 is useless (nobody can ABX them).

CHANGELOG:
LAME 3.98.4    March 22 2010

full changelog here http://lame.cvs.sourceforge.net/viewvc/lame/lame/doc/html/history.html

LAME 3.92    April 14 2002
â€¢Alexander Leidinger:  add non linear psymodel (compile time option, disabled by default), workaround a bug in gcc 3.0.3 (compiler options, based upon suggestions from various people, see archives and changelog for more)
â€¢Steve Lhomme:  ACM wrapper (MS-Windows codec)
â€¢Steve Lhomme:  less memory copying on stereo (interleaved) input
â€¢Takehiro Tominaga: Inter-channel masking, enables with --interch x option
â€¢For buggy versions of gcc compiler (2.96*), back off on some of the advanced compiler options
